<br>
I have defended him and everything he's done, even when he didn't deserve it. He's a great artist, he's still my favorite, but that doesn't mean I have to like everything about him. Don't complain because he won't read it? That's silly. No one would complain about anything if they followed that logic. And telling people not to get angry about something because they'll never know makes even less sense. I am angry, you can't just turn it on and off.<br>
<br>
It doesn't bother me so much that he's slow or late, I can deal with that. But when he just tosses it aside because he got bored and decided he felt like doing something else, then THAT pisses me off. Stop stringing us along telling us one thing that's going to happen, then just go and decide you want to design videogames all of a sudden.<br>
<br>
Hey, I'm sure I'll get over it, and I'm sure he'll do a great job at whatever he ends up doing. I just don't like being lied to or being teased with future issues of BC dangled in front of my face that never seem to come out. I'm no less a fan of his work because of this, but I lost a LOT of respect for him because of this. His work is still great, but the person is the one who's pissing me off.<br>
<br>
If he can finally stick to what he's doing, and do it well, then I'm sure I'll get over this. But you have to earn respect, it's not automatic for being a good artist. <br>
<br>
